9. What is a Test Set?
Answer9- A test set is a portion of the dataset that is kept separate from the training process. It is used 
to evaluate the performance of a trained machine learning model.
The model does not see the test data during training. Therefore, testing provides a fair estimate of how 
well the model will perform on new and unseen data in real-world situations.
