Common Scaling Techniques
1. Standardization
Transforms data so that it has a mean of 0 and a standard deviation of 1.
2. Min-Max Scaling
Scales values between 0 and 1.
3. Normalization
Adjusts values to a common scale without distorting differences.
Scaling is an important preprocessing step because it helps machine learning models learn more 
effectively and produce better results.
